for nature's agency as the coworker of God. Embracing in this more elusive idea of nature in a world beset by environmental crisis, she suggests, will allow us to see nature not as a victim but as an ally in a common quest for re-attunement to the divine. Putting its protagonists into further dialogue with such classic authors as Augustine, Maximus the Confessor, Friedrich Schleiermacher, and William James, her study deconstructs the idea of pantheism and paves the way for a new natural theology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aNatural theology. 0aNaturexReligious aspects. 0aPhilosophy of nature. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / General.2bisacsh  acreation.  aexegesis.  ahistory of thought.  aidealism.  amysticism.  anature.  apanentheism.  apantheism.  atheology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361168940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503611689423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503611689.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070477-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020